Five men including two traditional healers allegedly involved in the trade of human body parts are expected to appear in the Makuya Periodical Court outside Thohoyandou in Limpopo. They allegedly dug up graves and stole remains for muti purposes. Police exhumed six graves to verify the allegations and found that four graves were tempered with and body parts stolen. The suspects aged between 20 and 42 were denied bail last month. The case is expected to be transferred to the Sibasa Regional Court for trial. About SABC Radio View all posts by SABC Radio